WEBVTT

00:38.429 --> 00:42.781
MINER: I found it!
I Found it Monty!

00:47.525 --> 00:50.572
MINER: I found it Monty!
I found it!

00:50.746 --> 00:54.576
I earned that bonus didn't I,
Monty?

00:54.750 --> 00:57.709
MONTGOMERY:
It's Montgomery.

01:05.978 --> 01:07.850
MONTGOMERY: And what makes
you think

01:08.024 --> 01:10.809
I've got the money

01:10.983 --> 01:12.463
for your outrageous bill?

01:12.637 --> 01:14.509
MINER: Well, we had a deal!

01:14.683 --> 01:17.164
MONTGOMERY: You think I'm
gonna get my hands dirty?

01:17.338 --> 01:19.122
[pistol hammer clicking]
Wonder if this works?...

01:19.296 --> 01:21.081
MINER What? No! [trigger clicks]

01:23.953 --> 01:24.823
MONTGOMERY:
I guess not...

01:24.997 --> 01:25.911
MINER: Are you crazy!?

01:27.435 --> 01:27.957
MONTGOMERY:
I guess I'll have to use mine

01:28.784 --> 01:29.393
MINER:
NO!

01:29.567 --> 01:30.090
[Gunshot]

01:31.047 --> 01:31.830
[women screaming]

01:35.486 --> 01:36.531
NELL FORD: Harriette
Alda Ford get over here!

01:40.056 --> 01:41.536
GRANDMA FORD:
Get back to your studies baby!

01:42.450 --> 01:42.972
MASTER FORD: Handsome!

01:43.712 --> 01:45.105
[horses trotting]

01:47.542 --> 01:49.196
MASTER FORD: Get Nell and my
daughter to safety, please!

01:53.504 --> 01:55.115
[horse neighs]

01:56.507 --> 01:58.379
JESSE JAMES:
Well Robert Ford...

01:58.553 --> 02:00.381
when you and your brother
offered to take Frank's position

02:00.555 --> 02:02.252
In this gang

02:02.426 --> 02:04.733
you never mentioned to me that
you had a baby sister.

02:07.344 --> 02:08.867
ROBERT FORD: Yeah well
this land's mine Jesse.

02:09.041 --> 02:11.174
CHARLIE FORD:
Don't worry about it, Jesse.

02:11.348 --> 02:12.697
There's enough in that
house to make it worth
the whole gang's time.

02:14.612 --> 02:15.787
NELL FORD: Come on. Come on
lets go back in the house...

02:15.961 --> 02:18.094
Lets go back in the house!

02:20.705 --> 02:23.665
MASTER FORD: I never expected
my sons to be riding up with

02:23.839 --> 02:26.407
THE Jesse James

02:26.581 --> 02:30.411
To what do I owe this honor
gentlemen?

02:35.720 --> 02:38.288
ROBERT: Charlie and I are your
flesh and blood, we're your kin!

02:38.462 --> 02:40.029
Alright now where's the will?

02:41.813 --> 02:45.643
Civil War ended 17 years ago
Mr. James.

02:46.601 --> 02:48.733
This is their land.

02:48.907 --> 02:52.911
They're gonna defend it
just like they fought
for their freedom.

02:53.085 --> 02:55.523
You can't hang on
to them old ways anymore.

02:57.264 --> 02:59.831
ROBERT: I WANT THE
WILL PA! WHERE IS IT!?

03:01.355 --> 03:02.834
SAMSON: You boys will
never get it like this.

03:06.621 --> 03:09.450
JESSE: I must be either
gettin' old, or stupid...

03:11.365 --> 03:13.410
Frank would have never let us
get tied into a family dispute.

03:13.584 --> 03:15.978
CHARLIE: Now Samson you
better put that thing down

03:16.152 --> 03:17.632
before you get somebody hurt.

03:19.155 --> 03:21.940
SAMSON: Charles... ain't
nobody gonna win this.

03:23.377 --> 03:25.030
JESSE:
We don't want any problems,

03:25.205 --> 03:26.815
and it'd be a real shame to put
a hole in that pretty vest.

03:26.989 --> 03:28.947
MASTER FORD:
Robert listen to me!

03:29.121 --> 03:32.037
♪[tense music swells]

03:33.909 --> 03:35.476
[window breaks]

03:35.650 --> 03:40.350
[gunshots]

03:46.138 --> 03:47.270
ROBERT:
PA!

03:54.843 --> 03:59.239
MASTER FORD: Don't do this
son! I just paid off the
bank. It's all ours now.

04:02.677 --> 04:04.244
ROBERT: Who's us?

04:06.507 --> 04:08.248
MASTER FORD:
It belongs to your mother.

04:09.945 --> 04:13.905
ROBERT: Nell is NOT my
mother! My mother is DEAD!

04:14.079 --> 04:16.256
Where is the will?!

04:18.649 --> 04:21.261
MASTER FORD: It's locked
in the bank. You'll never
get it out of that box.

04:24.916 --> 04:26.831
[gunshot]

04:35.318 --> 04:40.280
[Nell crying]

04:46.286 --> 04:48.592
[page turning]

04:59.690 --> 05:04.129
JACKSON: Montgomery South
became a champion of history

05:04.304 --> 05:08.569
when he unearthed this
civil war outlaw pistol
belonging to Jesse James

05:10.440 --> 05:14.183
from a haunted cavern mine
shaft near Ford Farm.

05:14.923 --> 05:15.837
[door opening]

05:17.708 --> 05:19.623
MONTGOMERY: It's good
doing business with ya...

05:21.712 --> 05:24.236
Don't be touchin' things
that don't belong to you.

05:26.630 --> 05:30.330
BEN FORD: Jackson
Please don't. Let's go.

05:34.986 --> 05:36.988
[brakes squeal]

05:37.162 --> 05:39.164
[car door opens]

05:40.949 --> 05:42.907
[car door slams]

05:46.171 --> 05:48.173
JACKSON: Why did we have to
come here this early dad?

05:48.348 --> 05:49.697
BEN: I'll tell you
on the way to school

05:49.871 --> 05:51.089
REBECCA FORD: Hey baby,
hey Jackson...

05:51.263 --> 05:53.353
baby is everything OK?

05:55.442 --> 05:57.748
MONTGOMERY: When they
get settled into the
Illinois plant...

05:57.922 --> 05:59.663
I want an accident.

06:01.186 --> 06:02.318
CLAY: Like what
kind of an accident?

06:06.191 --> 06:07.715
MONTGOMERY: I want him fired...

06:15.810 --> 06:17.289
or worse.

06:18.465 --> 06:19.857
SHERIFF ANGELA: Wait
right here

06:20.858 --> 06:22.817
[quirky music]

06:30.999 --> 06:35.395
SHERIFF ANGELA: Monty.
We need to talk about
our little project.

06:36.526 --> 06:38.223
In private.

06:39.573 --> 06:41.313
MONTGOMERY:
It's Montgomery ... Ma'am.

06:43.577 --> 06:48.277
[children rummaging
and whispering]

06:50.148 --> 06:54.805
[children cheering over
good grades]

07:17.001 --> 07:20.004
MRS. SMART: You all
did fairly well on your
civil war legend report.

07:20.178 --> 07:22.006
[bell ringing]

07:22.180 --> 07:23.921
Have a safe weekend!

07:24.095 --> 07:26.402
[children walking]

07:27.969 --> 07:30.798
MRS. SMART: Doniphan...
Doniphan?

07:31.799 --> 07:34.932
if you please, a moment.

07:35.106 --> 07:37.457
Mr. James,

07:37.631 --> 07:42.157
you're the only one that's
going to have to redo
the report this weekend.

07:42.331 --> 07:43.332
Otherwise it's an F.

07:43.506 --> 07:45.203
DONIPHAN: an F!?

07:45.377 --> 07:48.903
MRS. SMART: I googled it.
A True West Magazine blog?

07:49.077 --> 07:51.601
Really?

07:51.775 --> 07:55.649
Other than your name, Doniphan
James at the top, the entire
report is plagiarized.

07:57.999 --> 08:01.002
You are far better than this.

08:01.176 --> 08:02.960
One chance to make this up.

08:05.180 --> 08:08.575
Between you and me. No
copy. No paste. Do we
understand each other?

08:08.749 --> 08:10.490
DONIPHAN: Yes Ma'am

08:12.448 --> 08:14.972
MRS, SMART: Monday.
A civil war legend.

08:15.146 --> 08:17.671
From a unique light.

08:17.845 --> 08:21.283
I look forward to seeing
what you can do when you put
some effort into something.

08:23.503 --> 08:26.157
♪[lighthearted music]

08:29.160 --> 08:30.510
[locker slams]

08:50.442 --> 08:52.096
[bus door shutting]

08:54.011 --> 08:56.318
DONIPHAN: She didn't like my
True West Magazine report.

08:56.492 --> 09:00.583
I have to rewrite the
whole thing this weekend...
otherwise I get an "F"!

09:00.757 --> 09:02.759
[phone buzzing]
JACKSON: Alright look.

09:02.933 --> 09:04.718
This time I'm gonna help you
with your report.

09:07.459 --> 09:10.550
DONIPHAN: Hey Mom! I'm gonna
do my work on the bus. Then
I'm gonna head to Jackie's.

09:10.724 --> 09:14.554
LISA JAMES: Whoa there
cowboy. Tell me how you
did on your history report?

09:17.078 --> 09:20.560
DONIPHAN: It was on Civil
War. Definitely going to
ace it! No doubt. I promise!

09:22.387 --> 09:23.737
LISA: Doniphan...

09:23.911 --> 09:26.217
DONIPHAN: So,
can I go to Jackie's?

09:26.391 --> 09:29.743
LISA: Okay but listen.
Be home by dark. And son,
that means BEFORE dark...

09:30.700 --> 09:31.875
alright I love you.

09:32.049 --> 09:32.702
DONIPHAN: Alright, love you too.
Bye.

09:34.443 --> 09:37.620
Dude, I have the greatest
name for our club.

09:38.578 --> 09:41.145
"The James Gang!"

09:41.319 --> 09:44.366
JACKSON: Really? "The James
Gang"? You know Jesse James
did some pretty bad things?

09:44.540 --> 09:46.586
He fought for the South...

09:46.760 --> 09:49.763
How about... "The Jackson Five?"

09:51.591 --> 09:53.593
DONIPHAN: Dude, that wont work.
There's only three of us...

09:54.768 --> 09:55.769
JACKSON: Oh yeah...

09:59.294 --> 10:00.295
ROSE: Crush Much?

10:00.469 --> 10:02.514
HOPE: What? Shut up!

10:08.433 --> 10:10.653
TV[BOY]: You started this
whole end of the world

10:10.827 --> 10:14.178
world zombie apocalypse thing,
by digging up a freakin' box!

10:14.352 --> 10:17.268
TV[JOHN JACOBS]: We're in a
cemetery in Ford County Missouri

10:17.442 --> 10:20.228
I'm John Jacobs: Ghost Hunter.
Come with me.

10:20.402 --> 10:21.403
[door opens]

10:22.491 --> 10:24.667
DONIPHAN: Hey! Look Tobi!

10:24.841 --> 10:25.929
JOHN JACOBS: Paranormal
activity in this area
has definitely spiked.

10:26.103 --> 10:27.539
DONIPHAN:
Hey Tobi! Look!

10:27.714 --> 10:31.282
I'm John Jacobs: Ghost Hunter...
And I'm scared.

10:31.456 --> 10:33.502
DONIPHAN: I gotta ball!
I gotta ball! I gotta ball!

10:36.505 --> 10:38.768
DONIPHAN: Grandpa,
I'm gonna head over to Jackie's!

10:38.942 --> 10:39.813
[TV Plays]

10:39.987 --> 10:40.640
DONIPHAN: Hey Grandpa!

10:41.641 --> 10:42.946
GRANDPA EDDIE: Go on

10:43.120 --> 10:44.034
DONIPHAN: Did you take your
meds?

10:45.601 --> 10:47.864
GRANDPA: Don't you
worry about me!

10:48.038 --> 10:50.475
Hey! I don't know if your
cousin Pippin has taken
her driver's test yet.

10:50.650 --> 10:52.347
So stay off the road
just in case!

10:52.521 --> 10:54.871
JOHN JACOBS: I swear there's a
light over there in the back...

10:55.045 --> 10:56.264
DONIPHAN: You know its
all fake right?...

10:56.438 --> 10:58.658
GRANDPA: I know, I know!

10:58.832 --> 11:01.443
JOHN JACOBS: I can feel it
inside my bones...

11:01.617 --> 11:03.097
you can feel a chill
on the back of your neck...

11:03.271 --> 11:06.361
GRANDPA: That is
not how it happened to me...

11:12.280 --> 11:13.760
CRICKET: Donnie!

11:14.717 --> 11:16.284
Doniphan Lee James!

11:18.286 --> 11:20.592
Don't you ignore me!
I want to come with you.

11:20.767 --> 11:22.507
DONIPHAN: C'mon, Cricket...

11:22.682 --> 11:24.553
CRICKET: Hu-uh! You make
time for your little brother!

11:26.947 --> 11:30.298
DONIPHAN: All right, all
right... you can come. But
only if you can keep up!

11:30.472 --> 11:32.604
And not be a hindrance!

11:35.259 --> 11:37.697
[playful music]

11:45.313 --> 11:47.707
What's a hinder-dance?!!

12:14.342 --> 12:15.778
JACKSON: Lets do this!

12:17.954 --> 12:19.390
DONIPHAN: we're gonna
need the shovels.

12:20.914 --> 12:21.305
HOPE: Don't forget
about the tunes!

12:22.829 --> 12:25.092
[music kicks off louder]

12:39.236 --> 12:41.369
HOPE: The rock will roll!

13:01.563 --> 13:03.652
JACKSON: Dude, I'm so ready.

13:03.826 --> 13:05.697
DONIPHAN: This fort
is gonna be SO savage

13:05.872 --> 13:07.830
HOPE: It's gonna
be so spectacular

13:08.004 --> 13:09.049
DONIPHAN: Fo, sho, yo.

13:09.223 --> 13:10.311
HOPE: Fo, sho!

13:12.443 --> 13:14.271
JACKSON: How many times
do I have to tell you...
that is last century.

13:14.445 --> 13:17.057
DONIPHAN: Dude, you have told
me that a thousand times! ok?

13:17.231 --> 13:18.710
I like it!... C'mon lets go

13:18.885 --> 13:21.583
JACKSON: Okay Yeah,
let's go.

13:40.210 --> 13:40.950
DONIPHAN: COME ON!

13:41.124 --> 13:41.821
HOPE: LETS GO!

13:53.702 --> 13:55.922
JACKSON: So, what's
the plan?

13:56.096 --> 14:00.187
DONIPHAN & HOPE: A lot
of digging for the escape
tunnel-slash-alternate entrance.

14:01.318 --> 14:03.407
JACKSON: Right. Let's do it.

14:19.989 --> 14:21.382
JACKSON: What is that?

14:21.556 --> 14:22.818
HOPE: Curtains!

14:22.992 --> 14:24.994
DONIPHAN: That's... nice.

14:25.168 --> 14:26.300
JACKSON: [Sighs]

14:29.129 --> 14:30.957
JACKSON: I really want
to put an Xbox in here.

14:31.131 --> 14:33.133
DONIPHAN: Dude,
that's impossible.

14:33.307 --> 14:37.702
That would take a
really, really, REALLY
long extension cord.

14:39.704 --> 14:41.881
JACKSON: I'll take the inside
I guess.

14:44.709 --> 14:47.234
HOPE: I'll start the DJ-ing
and get to work on the back.

14:48.626 --> 14:53.153
♪you were in it again.
my best friend

14:54.806 --> 14:59.376
♪when you got in the way
thats okay

15:00.900 --> 15:05.556
♪we were living along
singin our best song

15:07.297 --> 15:11.736
♪then it got in the way
but that's okay

15:13.651 --> 15:16.306
♪cause they're never gonna
stop us! never gonna stop us!

15:16.480 --> 15:20.615
♪Never never gonna stop us
Never gonna stop us again

15:20.789 --> 15:25.446
♪Not with my best friend

15:25.620 --> 15:28.579
♪cause they're never gonna
stop us! Never gonna stop us!

15:28.753 --> 15:32.801
♪No they're never gonna stop
us ♪ Never gonna stop us again

15:32.975 --> 15:35.804
♪Not with my best friend

15:35.978 --> 15:37.545
[music stops]

15:43.725 --> 15:44.465
DONIPHAN: No, no, no!

15:45.335 --> 15:46.032
HOPE: Doniphan?

15:51.472 --> 15:52.429
Come on!

15:55.650 --> 15:57.347
HOPE: Are you ok?...

15:58.392 --> 15:59.915
What's this?

16:00.089 --> 16:03.832
DONIPHAN: It's a big hole.
That's what it is.

16:04.006 --> 16:05.703
If we dig any deeper,
the whole fort will collapse.

16:05.877 --> 16:08.489
HOPE: Well, hold on.
Maybe we can use it?

16:08.663 --> 16:12.058
You know, incorporate it into
the fort? How deep does it go?

16:12.232 --> 16:14.538
DONIPHAN: I don't know,
it's a giant black hole.

16:14.712 --> 16:15.670
HOPE: Donnie give me
the flashlight.

16:20.762 --> 16:22.285
[flashlight clicks on]

16:25.810 --> 16:29.379
HOPE: There's something
in there. It's a chain? Or...

16:29.553 --> 16:31.729
maybe it's a necklace?

16:35.559 --> 16:37.997
DONIPHAN: Ah, it's stuck!
Jackson Help me!

16:39.346 --> 16:40.042
DONIPHAN: [grunts]

16:41.000 --> 16:42.653
DONIPHAN: Ew Gross!

16:42.827 --> 16:44.133
[suspensful music]

16:45.265 --> 16:47.006
HOPE: Really? Come on, guys.

16:48.355 --> 16:50.313
Aw, Isn't that cute?
It's a heart!

16:50.487 --> 16:52.924
DONIPHAN & JACKSON: Cute!?

16:53.099 --> 16:55.362
JACKSON: We call the sheriff!
This could be a murder
victim or a missing person

16:55.536 --> 16:57.668
or someone off the side of
one of those old milk cartons!

16:57.842 --> 17:00.280
DONIPHAN: Great...

17:00.454 --> 17:03.196
HOPE: This girl's been here
for a long time and she
sure ain't going anywhere.

17:03.370 --> 17:06.590
No rush. Maybe she's got a cool
ring or something?

17:09.115 --> 17:11.987
DONIPHAN: Okay, leave it
alone. I say we don't call
the cops or do anything at all

17:12.161 --> 17:15.599
until we talk to my mom.
Because somebody was basically
buried in Jackie's backyard!

17:15.773 --> 17:18.037
JACKSON: Hope you can't
just rob a dead person!

17:18.211 --> 17:20.735
HOPE: What's she gonna do?
Get angry?

17:20.909 --> 17:22.345
JACKSON: Well how do you
know it's a girl?

17:22.519 --> 17:24.782
HOPE: She's got a cool
necklace... duh

17:28.395 --> 17:30.788
JACKSON: ...None of this
will make a difference

17:32.442 --> 17:37.099
[Ominous music swells]

17:42.931 --> 17:45.629
DONIPHAN: Dude, you're not
gonna catch anything...
there isn't even a hook.

17:45.803 --> 17:47.066
JACKSON: I know...

17:48.719 --> 17:51.505
DONIPHAN: Okay, so what's the
deal with you right now!?

17:53.115 --> 17:54.377
JACKSON: My family is moving,
we leave monday.

17:56.945 --> 17:59.295
DONIPHAN: What? Why?

18:01.515 --> 18:03.256
HOPE: Where?

18:03.430 --> 18:06.607
JACKSON: My dad got laid off.
He got a job offer in Illinois.

18:06.781 --> 18:08.783
Montgomery told my
dad this morning.

18:08.957 --> 18:11.046
DONIPHAN: And your just now
telling me this?

18:11.220 --> 18:12.830
JACKSON: I guess I didn't think
it would sound so bad

18:13.004 --> 18:15.529
after finding a dead guy
in a hole under our fort.

18:15.703 --> 18:17.618
DONIPHAN: You were wrong.

18:19.750 --> 18:21.100
JACKSON: I was wrong.

18:23.798 --> 18:26.061
HOPE: There's gotta be
something that can be done.

18:26.235 --> 18:30.283
JACKSON: My Dad lost
his job. I can't do
anything, I'm just a kid!

18:32.285 --> 18:34.417
DONIPHAN: Monday?...

18:36.898 --> 18:40.684
CRICKET: It's dark outside.

18:41.468 --> 18:43.426
[door opens]

18:43.600 --> 18:45.733
DONIPHAN: Mom! Mom! We
were at our base, and we
found some skeleton...

18:45.907 --> 18:48.605
cracked and gross...
and we gotta call someone..

18:48.779 --> 18:51.391
Mom mom, we were at our
base, digging and we found...

18:51.565 --> 18:53.393
and we busted through
some sinkhole and we
found this skeleton

18:53.567 --> 18:56.309
with a crusty old key,
and a chain.

18:56.483 --> 18:58.572
And Jackson said he
has to leave town, he cant move-

18:58.746 --> 18:59.834
LISA JAMES: Stop!

19:00.008 --> 19:01.314
Just stop!

19:02.271 --> 19:04.273
you lied to me

19:04.447 --> 19:08.059
Doniphan Lee James!
I spoke to your teacher.

19:08.234 --> 19:13.108
You failed your report? Of all
people and of all things? you?

19:13.282 --> 19:15.328
DONIPHAN:But Mom, we found
this old skeleton with
a key in its hand, and-

19:15.502 --> 19:17.678
GRANDPA: Key?
Let me see that key!

19:17.852 --> 19:21.421
LISA: I don't care! Why
would you lie to me?
Why are you doing this?

19:22.422 --> 19:23.597
Only honest Abe knows.

19:24.728 --> 19:26.556
Don't you pull that on me.

19:26.730 --> 19:29.733
That stupid little phrase has
haunted us for generations.

19:29.907 --> 19:34.564
You will not end up like
every other failed James
man in this family!

19:35.696 --> 19:37.263
[doorbell rings]
[Tobi barks]

19:37.437 --> 19:40.091
I'll help him with the report.
[doorbell rings]

19:40.266 --> 19:44.879
It should be on Jesse
James. He is his great,
great, great grandfather.

19:46.794 --> 19:48.404
DONIPHAN: Did you all miss
the whole "dead body" thing?

19:48.578 --> 19:50.014
LISA: No dad! And Doniphan
I don't wanna hear another lie!

19:50.189 --> 19:53.148
DONIPHAN: It's a dead body mom!-
LISA: ENOUGH!

19:53.322 --> 19:57.718
GRANDPA: that's something
this family knows. We can use
that to get his report up.

20:00.155 --> 20:01.765
REBECCA: Hope this
isn't a bad time.

20:01.939 --> 20:06.030
LISA: No, Rebecca.
It's fine. Come on in

20:06.205 --> 20:08.381
BEN: I was hoping
to speak to Eddie.

20:08.555 --> 20:10.209
LISA: We can all sit right
here and talk, Ben.

20:10.383 --> 20:12.689
JACKSON: Did they all just miss
the entire dead body thing?

20:13.908 --> 20:15.562
GRANDPA: Whats up?

20:15.736 --> 20:18.652
BEN FORD: Montgomery won.
He fired me at the plant today.

20:21.176 --> 20:25.267
Well, actually, he concocted
some way to get me to transfered
out of town... to Illinois.

20:27.269 --> 20:30.011
REBECCA: He's forcing
Ben, Jackson and I
from our home Lisa.

20:30.185 --> 20:32.143
He's gonna get the house.

20:33.580 --> 20:35.799
JACKSON: Why would he
want OUR house?

20:35.973 --> 20:38.237
GRANDPA: It's not the
house he wants, it's
what's under that property.

20:39.020 --> 20:40.369
BEN: What? Empty caves?

20:40.543 --> 20:42.284
GRANDPA: OH They're not empty.

20:42.458 --> 20:44.895
We have been under that man's
thumb as long as I can remember

20:45.069 --> 20:47.942
and paying rent on property that
I know belongs to our family.

20:48.116 --> 20:49.639
LISA: No one has ever proven
that Ben. [Tobi barking]

20:49.813 --> 20:51.989
REBECCA: And no one ever will.
[Tobi barking]

20:52.163 --> 20:56.037
LISA: Maybe it's time
that we all move... and
put the curse to rest.

20:57.430 --> 20:59.040
BEN: What about the kids?

20:59.214 --> 21:00.650
LISA: For the kids. [Tobi
barking] Tobi shut up!

21:00.824 --> 21:01.869
HOPE: Why can't you
just get another job?

21:02.043 --> 21:04.524
BEN: I wish I could.

21:04.698 --> 21:08.136
Montgomery owns this town.
He has everyone thinking
that I killed Doniphan's dad.

21:09.833 --> 21:12.967
My best friend?
I can't go nowhere

21:14.142 --> 21:15.274
LISA: Not everyone Ben.

21:17.667 --> 21:21.018
REBECCA: He uses this against
Ben every time he tries
to stop working for him.

21:21.192 --> 21:23.369
BEN: He has me on a noose.

21:23.543 --> 21:25.849
GRANDPA: We all know
that wasn't your fault!

21:26.023 --> 21:27.634
BEN: The town doesn't.

21:27.808 --> 21:29.288
LISA: But we do!

21:29.462 --> 21:32.421
[toby barks]
[triumphant music]

21:33.944 --> 21:34.902
LISA: And that's all that
matters.

21:36.773 --> 21:41.082
That cave, the Treasure,

21:41.256 --> 21:45.086
they are nothing but a
dark curse that comes
after every James boy

21:45.260 --> 21:47.436
just to break him, destroy him.

21:48.219 --> 21:49.308
[Tobi Barks]

21:50.221 --> 21:52.093
Look it's time to move.

21:52.267 --> 21:54.661
GRANDPA: This whole town will
always be under Monty's buckle

21:54.835 --> 21:58.926
until someone says enough
is enough. [Tobi barking]

21:59.100 --> 22:00.362
LISA: TOBI SHUT UP!

22:01.885 --> 22:03.887
BEN: He always beats
us to the punch.

22:04.061 --> 22:07.500
GRANDPA: Ya know every James
boy has tried to make it right

22:07.674 --> 22:08.979
and failed...

22:09.153 --> 22:11.852
Maybe we should all move away.

22:12.026 --> 22:16.683
Tuck tail and run. Or maybe we
finally have a reason to fight.

22:16.857 --> 22:20.861
LISA: I will not lose my son
like we lost his father.

22:21.035 --> 22:22.776
[Tobi barking]

22:22.950 --> 22:26.432
I'm NOT doing this again.
We're NOT doing this again.

22:26.606 --> 22:31.262
GRANDPA: Well I guess I'm just
an old man, dreamin' old dreams.

22:36.050 --> 22:39.445
LISA: Think it's time you go
get started on that book report.

22:39.619 --> 22:44.363
[Tobi barking]

22:45.276 --> 22:46.756
LISA: TOBI SHUT UP!

22:46.930 --> 22:48.889
[whimpering]

22:49.803 --> 22:53.067
[Triumphant music]

22:53.241 --> 22:58.202
[sounds of battle]

23:01.815 --> 23:03.251
DONIPHAN: Man, this sucks.

23:03.425 --> 23:05.035
JACKSON: Tell me about it.

23:18.962 --> 23:20.877
HOPE: There's gotta be
something we can do.

23:25.316 --> 23:27.449
[mysterious music]

23:31.366 --> 23:33.194
[chest clicks open]

23:36.980 --> 23:38.939
[rummaging]

23:47.251 --> 23:50.385
[dramatic music]

24:02.789 --> 24:06.967
GRANDPA: "horse walks into a
bar, the bartender sees him...

24:08.969 --> 24:11.362
and?..."

24:11.537 --> 24:16.237
DONIPHAN: "...why the long face?
Grandpa. Why the long face?"

24:21.460 --> 24:23.157
GRANDPA: Yeah...

24:24.506 --> 24:25.551
Listen.

24:25.725 --> 24:28.379
DONIPHAN: Why the long face...

24:28.554 --> 24:32.166
GRANDPA: This is
purely to inspire your
homework assignment.

24:32.340 --> 24:34.081
Okay?

24:34.255 --> 24:38.607
Now no one ever came of
any good from this here book.

24:38.781 --> 24:43.438
But in the past our family
has gone after this lost
treasure for all wrong reasons.

24:45.527 --> 24:48.487
Monty knows the treasure
is still there

24:48.661 --> 24:53.274
otherwise he wouldn't be
spending all that money
going after it for so long.

24:55.711 --> 24:58.366
["Only Honest Abe Knows"]
Jesse wrote this on the
first page all by itself,

24:58.540 --> 25:01.325
like he meant to tease us.

25:01.500 --> 25:05.678
Take a look, take a look boy.

25:16.732 --> 25:20.301
Look at that son,
it's right here in the book!

25:22.651 --> 25:24.261
[page flips]

25:34.141 --> 25:36.230
HANDSOME: We best get a move on.

25:37.623 --> 25:40.364
NELL: Waited too long.
I can feel it.

25:40.539 --> 25:43.672
Them boys got what they
needed to know. What
they really wanted.

25:43.846 --> 25:46.283
HANDSOME: We got to try.
It's all we got.

25:46.457 --> 25:48.895
NELL: What we gonna do?

25:49.069 --> 25:50.810
A black woman is just gonna
walk all fancy right on
into that white man's bank

25:50.984 --> 25:52.638
and demand her property?

25:52.812 --> 25:55.075
HANDSOME: I promised
Master Ford I'd get you safe.

25:55.249 --> 25:58.208
How safe you gonna be, and
everyone else who lives
there, with nothing!?

26:00.907 --> 26:02.822
NELL: Ain't nothin' there
no more.

26:04.301 --> 26:06.042
[pistol hammer clicks]

26:06.216 --> 26:08.262
[coins rustling]

26:10.960 --> 26:12.788
JESSE: Let's make
this a quick one boys.

26:15.922 --> 26:18.054
[guitar music plays]

26:18.228 --> 26:20.448
[sounds of town talking
and working]

26:23.016 --> 26:24.452
[hammering]

26:24.626 --> 26:26.062
MAN: I missed you

26:26.236 --> 26:28.587
[guitar music continues]

26:43.297 --> 26:46.692
JESSE: The townsfolk don't
seem to appreciate our horses.

26:48.998 --> 26:51.131
BOY: Sheriff! over there!

26:51.914 --> 26:53.916
SHERIFF: Oh no!

26:55.091 --> 26:56.963
Hey! wake up! Go get the boys!

26:58.834 --> 27:01.315
JESSE: I don't know how you
ever talked me into this Robert?

27:01.489 --> 27:04.535
The only thing I want to do with
the law in this town is to get
to know the sheriff's daughter.

27:04.710 --> 27:06.929
ROBERT: South. Take me
to the lock boxes,

27:07.103 --> 27:11.107
in the back, C'mon lets
go! I want the lock box
that this key opens.

27:11.281 --> 27:14.633
Jesse, I got the window!
I got it!

27:14.807 --> 27:17.636
JESSE: I didn't mean you
really wanted to meet
the Sheriff's daughter.

27:23.032 --> 27:25.165
[gun hammer clicks]
ROBERT: Open it South!

27:25.339 --> 27:29.473
SOUTH: I... I can't.
It takes two keys...
matching keys to open it.

27:29.648 --> 27:34.348
Your father and your mother ...
Mrs Ford each have... had one.

27:37.351 --> 27:41.572
JESSE: We go now or you're
gonna open up a permanent
account at this bank!

27:42.356 --> 27:43.444
[pistol decocks]

27:45.098 --> 27:46.360
[hit]

27:49.668 --> 27:52.192
JESSE: I swear to god you're
gonna lead me to an early death.

27:52.366 --> 27:54.673
ROBERT: This box has the Ford
family name on it, alright?

27:54.847 --> 27:56.587
It's my Legacy.
It's mine by rights.

27:56.762 --> 27:58.546
JESSE: Sheriff's got a box
with your name on it as well.

27:58.720 --> 28:00.635
I don't think you want to
be dragging it around!

28:02.289 --> 28:03.377
HARRISON: WOHOO!

28:03.551 --> 28:04.552
[gunshot]

28:06.162 --> 28:09.688
[rapid gunshots]

28:12.995 --> 28:15.084
WOMAN: Hurry
give me my gun!

28:16.172 --> 28:18.348
[gunshot]

28:19.349 --> 28:20.699
[gunshots]

28:24.093 --> 28:24.920
[gunshot]

28:26.574 --> 28:28.794
[gunshots]

28:30.056 --> 28:32.798
[women screaming]

28:34.234 --> 28:35.365
[ghasp]

28:35.539 --> 28:36.889
[gunshots]

28:37.803 --> 28:41.067
[women screaming]

28:41.241 --> 28:43.722
[gunshots contiue]

28:46.812 --> 28:51.730
[trotting and gunshots]

28:55.298 --> 28:57.518
JESSE: We need a place to
hunker down! Some place to hide!

28:57.692 --> 29:00.129
HARRISON: There's a cave down
the valley! Know it pretty well.

29:00.303 --> 29:01.740
[gunshots]

29:01.914 --> 29:03.393
[man grunts]

29:05.308 --> 29:10.139
[gunshots]

29:22.108 --> 29:24.458
COWBOY: Dagnabbit!
Whats going on out here?

29:24.632 --> 29:25.459
[gunshots]

29:25.633 --> 29:27.243
COWBOY: TARNATION!

29:27.417 --> 29:28.375
[gunshot]

29:33.032 --> 29:36.165
[horses trotting through water]

29:40.256 --> 29:42.737
[energetic music]

29:46.001 --> 29:47.873
JESSE: C'mon boys!

29:50.527 --> 29:52.138
C'mon boys, into the hole!

29:57.273 --> 30:00.189
[frantic rustling]

30:02.322 --> 30:04.411
[horses neighing]

30:06.369 --> 30:08.067
[eerie music]

30:08.241 --> 30:09.198
[gunshot]

30:10.286 --> 30:12.419
JESSE: C'mon, C'mon...

30:12.593 --> 30:13.899
The horses are spooked!

30:14.073 --> 30:15.465
POSSE: There they are!

30:15.639 --> 30:18.512
[gunshots]

30:20.993 --> 30:23.909
[eerie music intensifies]

30:26.825 --> 30:29.262
[gunshots]

30:29.436 --> 30:30.916
[deep bassy sound]

30:33.701 --> 30:35.877
[NARRATION] GRANDPA: They
held up deep inside the cave

30:36.051 --> 30:39.141
with the whole town's money
and the box.

30:43.189 --> 30:47.933
Now legend tells the
Indians used to live in
that underground kingdom

30:48.107 --> 30:51.240
until the white man came and
killed them all,

30:51.414 --> 30:55.592
and made their home into
an underground mining operation.

30:55.766 --> 31:00.336
Well the ghosts of those Indians
still live in those caves.

31:00.510 --> 31:05.124
Jesse and Robert struck some
kind of deal with these spirits

31:05.298 --> 31:08.954
to show them a way out in
exchange for the treasure.

31:09.128 --> 31:13.088
HOPE: A deal
with Native American ghosts?

31:13.262 --> 31:17.353
GRANDPA: Legend tells...
spirits took the treasure

31:17.527 --> 31:21.923
but it wasn't enough.
They wanted blood.

31:22.097 --> 31:24.883
So, they took the
rest of Jesse's men.

31:25.927 --> 31:28.321
JACKSON: Let me see that!

31:28.495 --> 31:31.890
GRANDPA: Robert and Jesse
escaped but not before spirits
put a curse on the both of them.

31:35.719 --> 31:40.376
No one knows how they
got out, and no one's
ever seen the treasure.

31:42.248 --> 31:45.599
Thats why he left a trail of
clues and maps in his journal,

31:48.123 --> 31:51.344
but he left out just enough
information that no one
could go back without him.

31:54.086 --> 31:57.611
But as the curse would have
it Robert Ford shot Jesse in
the back and killed him dead

31:59.482 --> 32:02.398
before he'd tell anybody
where the treasure was...

32:02.572 --> 32:04.444
thunder crashes]

32:10.798 --> 32:13.279
[thunder]

32:16.456 --> 32:21.156
[sounds of water]

32:30.122 --> 32:33.647
JACKSON: So if we find the
treasure, we find the Will?

32:33.821 --> 32:37.303
And that proves that my family
has always owned the land?

32:37.477 --> 32:42.134
DONIPHAN: Look, my
great, great grandfather
failed. His son failed.

32:42.308 --> 32:46.965
My dad... he died! All for
this stupid cursed treasure!?

32:49.358 --> 32:51.230
What makes you think we'll
find it! What even makes
you think we'll make it?

32:51.404 --> 32:54.146
HOPE: Montgomery won't
stop here. Someone has
to step up and stop him.

32:54.320 --> 32:57.714
Is it dangerous?
Yeah. It is.

32:57.888 --> 33:00.587
But think of what it means
for both both of your families.

33:00.761 --> 33:03.590
Think of what it means
for all of us.

33:03.764 --> 33:05.592
your dad didn't have
this key.

33:05.766 --> 33:08.247
You're talking about a whole
unexplored underground world

33:08.421 --> 33:10.727
We don't know anything
about those caves.

33:10.901 --> 33:13.774
Look right here in this
book. It just looks like
a maze of who knows what?

33:13.948 --> 33:16.777
And what is that? Some
underground water tunnel thing?

33:16.951 --> 33:19.301
Guys we've never been in there!

33:19.475 --> 33:23.088
HOPE: This book has been
there. We have more clues
than anyone did before us.

33:23.262 --> 33:26.091
Jesse James always
intended to go back.

33:26.265 --> 33:28.919
Maybe the time has come.

33:29.094 --> 33:31.270
This sounds like the start
of an adventure.

33:31.444 --> 33:33.881
[thunder rubbling]

33:34.055 --> 33:37.798
[rain]

33:47.808 --> 33:51.203
JACKSON: Let's say we do
this. I'm not saying we
are, but let's just say.

33:51.377 --> 33:54.467
These caves run under
woods that go on forever,

33:54.641 --> 33:57.644
all the way to the river
and maybe beyond!

33:57.818 --> 33:59.863
How do we even know
where to start?

34:00.038 --> 34:01.604
HOPE: Where we found the key.

34:01.778 --> 34:05.347
DONIPHAN: The Fort. But,
even if we do find the lock box,

34:05.521 --> 34:07.915
it has two keys.
We only have one.

34:08.089 --> 34:11.745
JACKSON: This picture
shows a key that looks
like it goes to a gun?

34:11.919 --> 34:14.226
Like maybe it opens the handle.

34:14.400 --> 34:17.055
HOPE: Or maybe it's in
the handle.

34:17.229 --> 34:19.405
DONIPHAN: Hey! Montgomery found
a pistol with a white handle

34:19.579 --> 34:20.841
while he was mining in
the caves last month.

34:21.015 --> 34:22.277
It was all over everyone's
phone!

34:22.451 --> 34:25.019
HOPE: No telling where
he hid that.

34:25.193 --> 34:28.022
JACKSON: In plain sight. I
saw it this morning in a glass
case in Montgomery's office!

34:28.196 --> 34:29.763
It's right there!

34:29.937 --> 34:32.940
HOPE: You see? There's
something greater going on here.

34:33.114 --> 34:37.379
It's like fate picked
this moment to bring
all this together.

34:37.553 --> 34:40.730
All of us together,
to see what we're made of.

34:40.904 --> 34:44.908
To change history and
write a new legend.
Our legend. We need -

34:45.083 --> 34:46.649
CRICKET: -the second key!

34:46.823 --> 34:47.650
HOPE: CRICKET!

34:47.824 --> 34:49.478
HEY GET OUT OF HERE!

34:49.652 --> 34:53.047
JACKSON: OK, but the gun
is in a glass case, locked,

34:53.221 --> 34:56.442
in Montgomery's office! How
are we going to pull that off?

34:56.616 --> 34:58.618
DONIPHAN: If we can get
there, I can get us in.

34:58.792 --> 34:59.836
HOPE: What do you mean?

35:00.010 --> 35:01.795
DONIPHAN: I'm a James boy!

35:01.969 --> 35:04.450
I broke into school a few
times to change my grades.

35:04.624 --> 35:07.105
JACKSON: What?

35:07.279 --> 35:08.976
DONIPHAN: Middle School
didn't really work out.
They had an alarm system.

35:09.150 --> 35:11.587
JACKSON: You're a thief?!

35:11.761 --> 35:14.721
DONIPHAN: I never stole
anything. I just... changed
some grades. A few times.

35:14.895 --> 35:18.203
GRANDPA: Take the book
son. You're going to need it.

35:18.377 --> 35:21.597
It's everyday good deeds
that keep darkness at bay,

35:21.771 --> 35:23.338
and you kids are good.

35:23.512 --> 35:24.774
DONIPHAN: Come with us Grandpa!

35:24.948 --> 35:27.081
GRANDPA: I love a good
adventure

35:27.255 --> 35:30.476
but my time has passed.
I'd only hold you back.

35:30.650 --> 35:35.220
You can call me though. and
I'll be like Batman's Alfred,

35:35.394 --> 35:38.440
ready to hop on those
internet tubes and save the day.

35:38.614 --> 35:40.094
[laughing]

35:41.617 --> 35:43.750
DONIPHAN: You should
keep hold of the key.

35:43.924 --> 35:46.622
It will be a lot safer
with you, but just keep
it under your shirt.

35:48.189 --> 35:50.060
HOPE: Alright, now what?

35:51.932 --> 35:54.195
DONIPHAN: If we're
gonna get that pistol
out of Monty's office,

35:54.369 --> 35:57.329
we're gonna need some
wheels... Pippin.

35:57.503 --> 36:01.507
JACKSON: Pippin! She farts...
They really smell.

36:08.644 --> 36:13.345
[dramatic music]

36:23.964 --> 36:28.664
RED CLOAK: These are not
patient men I work for Monty.

36:30.405 --> 36:34.279
They get what they want...
they get results.

36:35.454 --> 36:38.761
They want. . . their treasure.

36:38.935 --> 36:40.676
MONTGOMERY: I have the key

36:40.850 --> 36:42.112
RED CLOAK: To what?

36:42.287 --> 36:43.984
MONTGOMERY: I'm working
on that.

36:44.158 --> 36:47.292
RED CLOAK: You made a deal.

36:47.466 --> 36:52.166
They are giving you three
days to hold up your end of it.

36:53.298 --> 36:55.604
MONTGOMERY: I need more
time than that!

36:55.778 --> 36:59.173
RED CLOAK: Three days, Monty!...

36:59.347 --> 37:02.655
after that we can no
longer protect you.

37:02.829 --> 37:05.092
[thunder]

37:14.275 --> 37:19.237
[ringing]

37:22.979 --> 37:24.503
PIPPIN: Hello?

37:24.677 --> 37:27.462
DONIPHAN: Pippin. It's Doniphan.
I need a huge favor.

37:27.636 --> 37:30.813
I need you to meet us at
the barn tomorrow right
after your driver's test.

37:30.987 --> 37:35.253
Oh and no pressure. You
HAVE TO PASS, or else
everything is ruined!

37:36.384 --> 37:37.429
...Okay?

37:38.212 --> 37:39.605
[door slams]

37:41.171 --> 37:42.260
MONTGOMERY: LISTEN UP!

37:44.958 --> 37:47.700
I'm only going to say
this once!

37:50.355 --> 37:53.183
You're gonna get in
there... you're gonna
tear these caverns apart!

37:53.358 --> 37:55.098
You're gonna find my treasure

37:58.276 --> 38:02.628
and I'm gonna pay you
double if that treasure
is in my hand by morning!

38:04.760 --> 38:06.240
Got it?

38:07.067 --> 38:09.287
ALRIGHT! GET TO WORK!

38:13.769 --> 38:15.118
[door closes]

38:15.293 --> 38:17.120
[playful music]

38:18.383 --> 38:20.254
CRICKET: I'm feeling kinda
hungry.

38:20.428 --> 38:24.040
Maybe I'll wake mom up and
ask her to cook us breakfast

38:24.214 --> 38:27.914
DONIPHAN: Jeez Cricket...
Fine! You can go!

38:28.088 --> 38:29.785
CRICKET: YES!

38:36.749 --> 38:39.534
JACKSON: What is he doing
here!? He can't come with us!

38:39.708 --> 38:41.406
DONIPHAN: I don't wanna
talk about it.

38:42.494 --> 38:44.234
CRICKET: I made
sandwiches

38:45.758 --> 38:47.455
DONIPHAN: Ready for one
last great adventure?

38:47.629 --> 38:49.631
JACKSON: this could be
a complete waste of time.

38:49.805 --> 38:51.807
HOPE: It could be the
best moment of our lives.

38:51.981 --> 38:53.069
DONIPHAN: You got
something better to do?

38:53.243 --> 38:55.420
JACKSON: [sigh]
Lets go

38:55.594 --> 38:57.247
DONIPHAN: If Pippin doesn't
pass this morning,

38:57.422 --> 38:59.685
this could be the shortest
adventure we've ever had.

39:01.948 --> 39:03.428
CRICKET: Hold this

39:03.602 --> 39:04.907
DONIPHAN: [grrr]

39:05.691 --> 39:08.302
[engine running]

39:08.476 --> 39:10.478
PIPPIN: I sweat when
I'm nervous...

39:10.652 --> 39:12.219
[fart]

39:13.046 --> 39:14.613
I fart too...

39:14.787 --> 39:16.615
INSTRUCTOR: OK.
Let's get THIS over with.

39:18.051 --> 39:19.095
[ignition squeals]

39:19.269 --> 39:21.489
PIPPIN: ooooh... sorry

39:21.663 --> 39:24.274
INSTRUCTOR: I need you
to pull to the end of the
block, and make a left

39:24.449 --> 39:25.798
PIPPIN: Okay.

39:30.063 --> 39:33.022
[silly music]

39:35.634 --> 39:37.505
[brakes squeak]

