1:03:03.475 --> 1:03:04.084
SAMUEL: AHH!

1:03:07.696 --> 1:03:09.263
[brakes grinding]

1:03:09.437 --> 1:03:12.789
[shots] PIPPIN: Say
hello to my little friend

1:03:16.053 --> 1:03:17.619
DONIPHAN: Everyone jump
in the water now!

1:03:17.794 --> 1:03:18.795
[tumbling]

1:03:19.230 --> 1:03:20.797
[shots]

1:03:25.802 --> 1:03:27.804
[splash]

1:03:28.979 --> 1:03:30.632
[splash]

1:03:31.372 --> 1:03:32.547
CRICKET: AHHH!

1:03:32.721 --> 1:03:33.722
[splash]

1:03:37.726 --> 1:03:38.815
[splash]

1:03:43.428 --> 1:03:45.212
[wack]

1:03:45.996 --> 1:03:47.824
SAMUEL: UGH AH!

1:03:49.564 --> 1:03:50.827
[splash]

1:03:51.828 --> 1:03:53.742
SAMUEL: [groans]

1:03:53.917 --> 1:03:56.093
CLAY: [straining]

1:03:56.267 --> 1:03:59.574
[brakes grinding]

1:04:04.275 --> 1:04:05.798
[loud boom]

1:04:06.843 --> 1:04:08.366
[loud boom]

1:04:16.374 --> 1:04:17.897
[wood breaking]

1:04:26.210 --> 1:04:27.776
CLAY: [grunts]

1:04:35.828 --> 1:04:38.875
[eerie music]

1:04:44.532 --> 1:04:45.403
CRICKET: [gasping]

1:04:51.104 --> 1:04:52.236
CRICKET: [coughing]

1:04:52.410 --> 1:04:53.672
HOPE: Cricket!!

1:04:53.846 --> 1:04:54.847
JACKSON: Hold on Cricket!

1:04:55.021 --> 1:04:56.893
[gasping and coughing]

1:05:00.635 --> 1:05:02.550
DONIPHAN: My hat!

1:05:04.465 --> 1:05:06.163
[coughing]

1:05:19.741 --> 1:05:22.614
PIPPIN: Come on Cricket!

1:05:22.788 --> 1:05:24.921
[coughing and gasping]

1:05:26.748 --> 1:05:28.446
BILLY: Blahh

1:05:28.620 --> 1:05:30.274
BILLY: Ugh! I'm
going to throw up.

1:05:31.579 --> 1:05:32.929
[silly music]

1:05:33.755 --> 1:05:36.193
CLAY: [laughing]

1:05:36.367 --> 1:05:38.543
SAMUEL: What is this crap?

1:05:39.848 --> 1:05:41.241
CLAY: oh, That's exactly
what it is.

1:05:41.415 --> 1:05:45.463
[squeaking]

1:05:46.681 --> 1:05:48.901
SAMUEL: Bat poop? ugh!

1:05:50.337 --> 1:05:52.252
BILLY: Those kids are
gonna to pay.

1:05:56.474 --> 1:05:58.955
CLAY: They'd take you
more seriously if you
weren't covered in guano.

1:06:00.826 --> 1:06:03.960
DONIPHAN: It's okay guys.
I got it!

1:06:09.487 --> 1:06:12.316
JACKSON: Really? so glad
you found your hat.

1:06:12.490 --> 1:06:15.058
Good thing your brother
didn't drown while you
were searching for it!

1:06:17.843 --> 1:06:19.671
Let it go man. You are
not Jesse James.

1:06:19.845 --> 1:06:22.761
DONIPHAN: I know!
It's my dad's hat.

1:06:23.762 --> 1:06:24.719
It's all I have left.

1:06:26.808 --> 1:06:28.897
JACKSON: You don't
get it! DONIPHAN: No
you don't understand.

1:06:29.072 --> 1:06:30.290
JACKSON: You are not
your dad! And you don't
wanna be Jesse James.

1:06:30.464 --> 1:06:32.858
He killed and stole for slavery.

1:06:33.032 --> 1:06:35.861
He was a bank robber,
not a super hero.

1:06:36.035 --> 1:06:36.862
Even his friends turned on him!

1:06:37.036 --> 1:06:38.733
HOPE: Jackson just stop!

1:06:38.907 --> 1:06:40.605
JACKSON: We are going
after money that Jesse stole.

1:06:40.779 --> 1:06:42.563
DONIPHAN: It was bank money
from Montgomery's family.

1:06:42.737 --> 1:06:45.523
JACKSON: It was the town's
money. That Jesse killed for.

1:06:45.697 --> 1:06:48.004
That makes it blood money!

1:06:48.178 --> 1:06:50.571
PIPPIN: Doesn't even matter
cause we're all gonna
die if we don't move now

1:06:52.138 --> 1:06:52.965
HOPE: There's an opening
here! Should we take it?

1:06:54.314 --> 1:06:55.359
PIPPIN: Maybe we should
check the book?

1:06:57.709 --> 1:07:00.190
DONIPHAN: Here you
figure it out.

1:07:00.364 --> 1:07:01.930
No no no!

1:07:06.674 --> 1:07:08.024
It's gone.

1:07:09.590 --> 1:07:11.897
JACKSON: You're my best friend,
but you always do this,

1:07:12.071 --> 1:07:15.205
but come this Monday, if we
even make it out of here alive,

1:07:15.379 --> 1:07:18.730
I won't be here to save your
brother. I won't be here to
help you with your report.

1:07:18.904 --> 1:07:20.819
I won't be here to finish
the fort.

1:07:20.993 --> 1:07:22.951
You have to finish what
you started this time.

1:07:30.916 --> 1:07:32.744
DONIPHAN: I lost the book.

1:07:32.918 --> 1:07:34.746
I almost killed my brother,

1:07:34.920 --> 1:07:37.053
and now we're lost
in Montgomery's cave

1:07:38.750 --> 1:07:40.491
Was I a hinder-dance?

1:07:44.669 --> 1:07:47.237
PIPPIN: Wow. I did not realize
I was signing up for some

1:07:47.411 --> 1:07:49.717
sappy, dramatic,

1:07:49.891 --> 1:07:53.112
deficating all over each other,
depressing brotherly moment.

1:07:53.286 --> 1:07:54.983
JACKSON: Is deficating
even a word?

1:07:56.333 --> 1:07:58.378
PIPPIN: Look. We've been shot
at,

1:07:58.552 --> 1:08:00.119
we've been attacked
by a dog, we've been
chased at high speeds,

1:08:00.293 --> 1:08:01.686
we've drowned in a lake,

1:08:01.860 --> 1:08:04.732
I'm cold and wet, my
hair is ruined,

1:08:04.906 --> 1:08:08.432
and not to mention if
we don't get going soon,
we're going to die!

1:08:10.216 --> 1:08:11.522
JACKSON: Well If I die I
don't have to move on Monday.

1:08:11.696 --> 1:08:13.698
CRICKET: You look stupid in that
hat anyway.

1:08:15.700 --> 1:08:17.615
Is that really why you wear it?

1:08:18.572 --> 1:08:19.617
DONIPHAN: Well...

1:08:19.791 --> 1:08:21.097
That hat is not dad Doniphan.

1:08:22.402 --> 1:08:23.447
Dad's in here.

1:08:30.671 --> 1:08:34.110
CRICKET: Are we gonna sit here
or are we gonna do something?

1:08:36.068 --> 1:08:37.330
DONIPHAN: You're
right little buddy.

1:08:39.158 --> 1:08:42.466
We've made it this far.
Further than dad ever did.

1:08:42.640 --> 1:08:44.772
CRICKET: Dad would
want us to go on.

1:08:44.946 --> 1:08:46.470
This is a great adventure.

1:08:47.993 --> 1:08:50.256
We're gonna stop
Jackson from leaving.

1:09:02.921 --> 1:09:05.053
DONIPHAN: Well, we can
swim toward the bad guys

1:09:05.228 --> 1:09:06.881
or follow this opening,
and see where it goes.

1:09:07.055 --> 1:09:08.144
CRICKET: Hm, Okay.

1:09:26.771 --> 1:09:28.816
BILLY: I'm coming for you kids!

1:09:28.990 --> 1:09:30.644
DONIPHAN: This better go
somewhere, fast!

1:09:30.818 --> 1:09:31.558
HOPE: It's up here guys!

1:09:31.732 --> 1:09:32.690
[shuffling]

1:09:36.041 --> 1:09:37.608
CRICKET: Have a nice day sir

1:09:37.782 --> 1:09:39.392
[sloshing]

1:09:41.699 --> 1:09:43.614
[wet cave sounds]

1:09:45.920 --> 1:09:47.400
DONIPHAN: C'mon, c'mon!
They're on their way.

1:09:51.274 --> 1:09:53.276
[panting]

1:09:54.277 --> 1:09:55.626
HOPE: It's a dead end!

1:09:55.800 --> 1:09:56.279
JACKSON: What are we
going to do now?

1:09:57.105 --> 1:09:57.889
CLAY: GET OFF!

1:09:58.063 --> 1:09:59.064
[splash]

1:10:00.021 --> 1:10:00.935
PIPPIN: We're gonna die.

1:10:02.110 --> 1:10:03.199
HOPE: There's no where to go.

1:10:03.938 --> 1:10:04.678
JACKSON: Oh! Come on!

1:10:04.852 --> 1:10:05.853
CRICKET: Nasty!

1:10:06.027 --> 1:10:07.028
PIPPIN: Oh gross!

1:10:07.203 --> 1:10:08.465
DONIPHAN: Pippin was that you?!

1:10:08.639 --> 1:10:10.031
PIPPIN: This is way beyond
nervous!

1:10:10.206 --> 1:10:11.511
HOPE: What is that smell?!

1:10:11.685 --> 1:10:12.382
DONIPHAN: It's coming from
over here.

1:10:13.731 --> 1:10:16.299
EVERYONE: OH!!!

1:10:17.691 --> 1:10:18.344
DONIPHAN: UGH!

1:10:19.606 --> 1:10:21.217
HOPE: What is that?!

1:10:21.391 --> 1:10:22.609
JACKSON: I think it's a
dead body?

1:10:22.783 --> 1:10:24.089
CRICKET: There's more
than one.

1:10:25.264 --> 1:10:28.049
HOPE: Looks like a... Miner?

1:10:28.224 --> 1:10:30.661
DONIPHAN: He hasn't been
dead very long, He's not
rotted like this guy.

1:10:30.835 --> 1:10:33.229
[somber music]

1:10:38.973 --> 1:10:40.497
Dad...

1:10:41.628 --> 1:10:43.021
HOPE: Doni, are you sure?

1:10:43.195 --> 1:10:44.240
DONIPHAN: I know this ring.

1:10:45.763 --> 1:10:46.720
I used to play with it while
he shaved.

1:10:48.069 --> 1:10:49.027
I'd pretend to be him in
the mirror.

1:10:50.855 --> 1:10:53.031
We found you...

1:10:59.385 --> 1:11:00.995
[from distance]
CLAY: LIGHT!

1:11:01.169 --> 1:11:02.736
I need more light in here.

1:11:04.869 --> 1:11:06.087
JACKSON: Guys, quick,
they're coming! Turn
off your head lamps.

1:11:07.611 --> 1:11:09.700
CRICKET: Are we all going
to die like you dad?

1:11:10.744 --> 1:11:11.441
[click]

1:11:14.357 --> 1:11:17.055
SAMUEL: Hey, it still
works. The bat poop must
have water-proofed it!

1:11:17.229 --> 1:11:20.014
BILLY: Hey, hey, you could
probably sell that!

1:11:20.188 --> 1:11:22.495
SAMUEL: You think
Montgomery would invest?
Business Partner-wise?

1:11:22.669 --> 1:11:23.366
BILLY: yeah

1:11:25.455 --> 1:11:28.327
CLAY: No one is going to
wipe crap across their
phones, you idiots!

1:11:28.501 --> 1:11:29.589
Shut up! C'mon!

1:11:31.374 --> 1:11:32.113
LIGHT!

1:11:32.288 --> 1:11:33.289
BILLY: Jerk...

1:11:35.987 --> 1:11:40.992
[whispering]

1:11:46.998 --> 1:11:50.958
[mystical music]

1:12:49.408 --> 1:12:52.368
BILLY: Man, What
died up in here?

1:12:54.587 --> 1:12:57.111
YOU know who died up in here.

1:12:58.112 --> 1:12:59.636
Well ... some anyway.

1:13:01.812 --> 1:13:03.204
SAMUEL: This don't make
any sense. Did we miss
something back there?

1:13:03.379 --> 1:13:05.163
BILLY: No, there isn't
anything to miss.

1:13:05.337 --> 1:13:06.860
SAMUEL: Well, they couldn't
have just up and disappeared!

1:13:07.034 --> 1:13:08.384
BILLY: Well, that's just what
Jesse James did.

1:13:13.127 --> 1:13:15.216
CLAY: Wet footprints.

1:13:16.522 --> 1:13:18.394
SAMUEL: They went through
the wall?

1:13:18.568 --> 1:13:21.092
BILLY: No ya idiot!
They just vanished?

1:13:21.266 --> 1:13:25.401
CLAY: Well lookie there.
May just earn that
bonus after all boys.

1:13:30.841 --> 1:13:33.409
[wind]
[eerie music]

1:13:37.108 --> 1:13:40.024
CRICKET: Awwwwe

1:13:50.295 --> 1:13:52.253
Wicked!

1:13:56.170 --> 1:13:58.564
HOPE: How many are there?

1:14:00.131 --> 1:14:01.698
JACKSON: Who are they?

1:14:15.102 --> 1:14:17.801
[grunting]

1:14:21.152 --> 1:14:23.110
CLAY: Get up here! before we
lose them.

1:14:23.284 --> 1:14:24.938
BILLY: Oh god that stinks.

1:14:25.112 --> 1:14:25.809
[grunting]

1:14:30.509 --> 1:14:32.729
[grunting]

1:14:32.903 --> 1:14:33.991
Guys...

1:14:35.862 --> 1:14:36.863
CLAY: Bring the light.

1:14:37.037 --> 1:14:39.170
BILLY: no! no. no

1:14:39.344 --> 1:14:41.041
SAMUEL: we're coming for you!!!

1:14:41.215 --> 1:14:43.000
BILLY: Hey guys!...
SAMUEL: You're gonna pay!

1:14:43.174 --> 1:14:43.870
[page flips]

1:14:45.176 --> 1:14:47.004
[gunshots]

1:14:47.178 --> 1:14:48.005
[loud bang]

1:14:48.179 --> 1:14:49.223
JESSE: AH!

1:14:51.704 --> 1:14:54.490
JESSE: Boys hold your fire!
They only need one shot
to know where we're at!

1:14:56.230 --> 1:14:57.971
HARRISON: I didn't think I
was gonna die today.

1:14:58.145 --> 1:15:00.583
I only have enough rounds for
maybe twelve more shots.

1:15:01.540 --> 1:15:02.889
ROBERT: What's next?

1:15:05.413 --> 1:15:06.589
JESSE: They're not man
enough to come in here.
They're gonna starve us out!

1:15:06.763 --> 1:15:08.068
HARISON: We ain't gonna starve.

1:15:08.242 --> 1:15:10.157
JESSE: Why ain't we gonna
starve?

1:15:10.331 --> 1:15:11.637
HARRISON: Me and my
brothers, we've been all
through these caverns.

1:15:12.769 --> 1:15:14.945
There's water. We can swim out.

1:15:16.642 --> 1:15:18.252
ROBERT: From the rear!
we can ambush them from behind!

1:15:18.426 --> 1:15:21.908
JESSE: what are you gonna choke
'em out? Guns don't swim.

1:15:22.082 --> 1:15:24.520
HARRISON: Wet powder means
no fire.

1:15:25.651 --> 1:15:27.523
[eerie music]

1:15:35.139 --> 1:15:38.490
[gunshots]

1:15:44.670 --> 1:15:45.541
HARRISON: AHHH!
[gunshot]

1:15:49.196 --> 1:15:50.546
[gunshots]

1:15:51.416 --> 1:15:53.549
[deep bassy sound]

1:16:18.138 --> 1:16:21.620
[eerie strings]

1:16:22.490 --> 1:16:24.971
[growling]

1:16:38.550 --> 1:16:39.812
SAMUEL: Did you put these here?

1:16:43.120 --> 1:16:44.077
CLAY: NO!?...

1:16:48.386 --> 1:16:49.996
[growling]
[screams]

1:16:50.170 --> 1:16:51.171
PIPPIN: What happened?

1:16:51.345 --> 1:16:53.043
JACKSON: I don't know.

1:16:53.217 --> 1:16:54.871
CRICKET: Maybe it's gonna
bury us like those Indians?

1:16:56.002 --> 1:16:58.265
HOPE: Uh, Native Americans?

1:16:59.876 --> 1:17:01.834
JACKSON: Guys! It's
Abraham Lincoln!

1:17:02.966 --> 1:17:04.402
PIPPIN: That's impossible!

1:17:05.925 --> 1:17:07.361
HOPE: No it's not.
It's right there.

1:17:07.535 --> 1:17:08.885
JACKSON: It's like a small
Mount Rushmore,

1:17:09.059 --> 1:17:10.408
CRICKET: only it's just him.

1:17:10.582 --> 1:17:13.629
DONIPHAN: Honest. Abe. Knows.

1:17:13.803 --> 1:17:16.893
Guys, Get it?
It's a play on words!

1:17:17.067 --> 1:17:19.765
Honest Abe's nose!

1:17:19.939 --> 1:17:21.767
It was right under
his nose all this time.

1:17:21.941 --> 1:17:24.117
HOPE: Does that one look
like Papa Smurf?

1:17:24.291 --> 1:17:28.905
DONIPHAN: what? no.
Look right there! It's
a pile of ... clothes??

1:17:29.079 --> 1:17:30.689
JACKSON: That's gotta
be it! Let's climb
down there and get it!

1:17:30.863 --> 1:17:32.473
PIPPIN: Uh, can you CLIMB
a rope?

1:17:32.648 --> 1:17:34.127
CRICKET: You can
lower me down.

1:17:35.259 --> 1:17:36.652
HOPE: And I'll go with him.

1:17:39.132 --> 1:17:40.133
It's Okay.

1:17:42.832 --> 1:17:45.008
JESSE: They must really want
their money back! You don't
ever go through lock boxes!

1:17:45.182 --> 1:17:48.098
Frank knew not to go
through lock boxes.
I blame you for this!

1:17:48.272 --> 1:17:50.361
you gave them too much
time to gather their men!

1:17:50.535 --> 1:17:52.276
CHARLIE: You got the loot!

1:17:52.450 --> 1:17:53.886
JESSEL What good's the loot
do me if I can't spend it!?

1:17:54.060 --> 1:17:56.454
ROBERT: Ah! Quit cha
belly achin'..You...

1:17:56.628 --> 1:17:58.456
JESSE: I blame you for this
Robert Ford! This is your
fault! It's your fault!

1:17:58.630 --> 1:17:59.892
ROBERT: It's my father's fault!

1:18:00.066 --> 1:18:01.546
JESSE: Don't you ever sass
me boy!

1:18:05.245 --> 1:18:06.551
JACKSON: We have to go
one at a time.

1:18:07.770 --> 1:18:08.945
DONIPHAN: I gotchu okay?

1:18:10.729 --> 1:18:11.861
Just keep looking at me.

1:18:15.255 --> 1:18:17.518
PIPPIN: They can't be far
behind, we gotta hurry!

1:18:22.132 --> 1:18:24.003
JACKSON: Jesse and
Robert stood right here.

1:18:24.177 --> 1:18:27.050
DONIPHAN: Jesse and
Robert were trapped right here.

1:18:28.965 --> 1:18:31.881
HOPE: Jesse and Robert must
have been naked here. Weird!

1:18:38.714 --> 1:18:40.541
Well I'll be...

1:18:44.894 --> 1:18:46.678
How on earth?!

1:18:46.852 --> 1:18:48.898
It looks just like him.
Without the hat.

1:18:49.072 --> 1:18:50.769
ROBERT: Wondered if someone
chiseled him out?

1:18:51.857 --> 1:18:54.207
Only honest Abe knows ...

1:18:55.295 --> 1:18:58.298
Only honest Abe knows.

1:18:58.472 --> 1:18:59.299
[eerie noise]

1:18:59.473 --> 1:19:00.474
[growling]

1:19:03.434 --> 1:19:05.001
EVERYONE: C'mon we gotta go!
we gotta get out of here!

1:19:07.481 --> 1:19:10.789
JESSE: We're Swimmin' outta
here boys! Just like Harrison
said, It's right there!

1:19:10.963 --> 1:19:13.270
JESSE: No coins! we hide
the coins over there!

1:19:13.444 --> 1:19:15.489
Anything that weighs you
down, leave it! We'll
come back for it later.

1:19:15.663 --> 1:19:16.664
[deep bassy sound]

1:19:20.233 --> 1:19:21.974
DONIPHAN: they got out
somehow because the pistol

1:19:22.148 --> 1:19:23.933
made it from here to the
room with the wagon.

1:19:24.107 --> 1:19:25.064
JACKSON: A secret
way out from here?!

1:19:27.414 --> 1:19:29.808
Looks like they stripped off
everything that was heavy.

1:19:30.983 --> 1:19:32.289
They must have went underwater.

1:19:34.421 --> 1:19:36.162
HOPE: Which must lead
to the lake, and the
room with the wagon!

1:19:36.336 --> 1:19:38.817
JACKSON: It's a puddle,
which is under our fort!

1:19:38.991 --> 1:19:40.514
PIPPIN: So that
must be the way out!

1:19:42.299 --> 1:19:43.256
DONIPHAN: The same way out
Jesse took to escape the posse!

1:19:43.430 --> 1:19:44.867
JACKSON: I saw that in the book.

1:19:45.041 --> 1:19:46.782
The top hat, that must
be my boy Abe!

1:19:48.566 --> 1:19:50.916
DONIPHAN: An underwater
passage... thats it!
thats our way out!

1:19:53.266 --> 1:19:57.096
PIPPIN: I'm here for driving
purposes, not diving,

1:19:57.270 --> 1:20:01.144
and my hair is so
rashed already.

1:20:01.318 --> 1:20:03.929
HOPE: The treasure! It was
under the clothes!

1:20:04.103 --> 1:20:07.193
Sacks of coins! More
than we can carry!

1:20:07.367 --> 1:20:10.066
CRICKET: And there's old
guns and quick draw holsters!

1:20:10.240 --> 1:20:11.328
[rattling]

1:20:11.502 --> 1:20:12.503
... and a box?!

